description:
&lt;p&gt;Band 5 Endoscopy Staff Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At University Hospitals Birmingham, we have one of the biggest endoscopy departments in the country, spanning four hospitals, providing a wide range of diagnostic and therapeutic procedures, including emergency out of hours endoscopy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have opportunities across all 4 hospitals, for Band 5 nurses to join our friendly and dynamic teams. Endoscopy is an ever – changing speciality, and this job will give you the chance to become a specialised nurse, in an area where no 2 days are the same. Whether you are newly – qualified, or an experienced nurse looking for an exciting new challenge, Endoscopy will provide you with a structured training plan, and give you the tools you need to become an expert nurse in a variety of conditions and procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pride ourselves on being a supportive team, ensuring that staff satisfaction and supporting a healthy work – life balance are high on our priorities. If you’d like to join a caring and nurturing team, with plenty of learning and development opportunities, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have any questions please call:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GHH - Mandy Harrison – Clinical Manager – 0121 424 9362&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SOL – Amanda Hemming – Clinical Manager – 0121 424 5394&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BHH – Rose Riley – Clinical Manager – 0121 424 9188&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;QEH – Fiona Thomas – Clinical Manager – 0121 371 3831&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shortlisted candidates will be contacted within two weeks of receipt of their application to arrange an interview.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At University Hospitals Birmingham we support flexible working and welcome applications from nurses seeking flexible working opportunities and family friendly working hours&lt;/p&gt;
